snippet.title: SortTV
snippet.description: Automatically sorts TV show episodes into an organised directory structure. Can optionally move non-episodes into a separate directory. Also optional integration with xbmc (notification and library update). dir structure:[show]/[season x]/[eps]

snippet.title: ShowDown
snippet.description: ShowDown is a simple yet powerful tool for automating the process of finding and downloading new episodes of your favorite shows as they air. Simply choose your shows from the ever growing list of supported shows, then let ShowDown do the rest.

snippet.title: R-Extension for NetLogo
snippet.description: This extension connects the simulation platform NetLogo with the statistical analysis software R. It adds some new primitives to NetLogo, which offers the interchange of data with R and the call of R functions from NetLogo. See the documentation for more details. There is also the possiblity to open an Interactive R Shell from NetLogo. _______________________________________ Please have also a look on our info page about other NetLogo extensions at http://www.uni-goettingen.de/en/315075.html. _______________________________________ Please cite this software in scientific publications as: Thiele, JC; Grimm, V (2010). NetLogo meets R: Linking agent-based models with a toolbox for their analysis. Environmental Modelling and Software, Volume 25, Issue 8: 972 - 974

snippet.title: AnimeBrowser
snippet.description: AnimeBrowser is a java multiplatform program designed to help people who are accustomed to watch a lot of anime series. You can define episodes series you are looking for, then AnimeBrowser will search for it on some very popular websites.

snippet.title: Auto TV to Sabnzbd
snippet.description: A php script to list your favourite tv series and searsch NZBMatrix.com or nzbd.org or both for new episodes. It is built on Kohana 3 framework. And can output RSS feed for Sabnzbd. And much more.
